PLib 6.x.x
Documentation instructions at the bottom.
-------------------------
PLib is a C library made to make parsing command line arguments easier.
The Latest version of plib uses zero memory allocation and is a completely
header-only library which makes compilation a breeze.

To use PLib in your codebase you will just require the plib6.h file from this 
repo, everything else is not neccercery. see examples/README.md for the full 
documentation.

All features:
- Header only library 
- Under 170 lines of code.
- Only 2 functions.
- Does not use any malloc/free or any stdlib.h for that matter 
- Optimized for user control.
- Intuitive variable recycling system used to return argument value.
- Very simple usage and installation.
- Full error handling.
- Extensive features.

--------------------------
Quickstart: 
You only require the plib6.h file which you can download like so:

Edge:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/9JH1/plib/refs/heads/main/plib6.h

Stable:
wget https://github.com/9JH1/plib/blob/6.0.4/plib6.h

The following is all that is required for basic implementation:
--------------------------
#include "plib6.h"

int 
main(int argc, char *argv[])
{
	// Create argument array 
	struct plib_Argument pl[1] = {
		/* flag,    short name,  description */
		{ "--test", "-t",       "Description here!" }
	};

	// Initialize arguments 
	plib_CreateArgCount(pl);

	// Actually parse the arguments
	plib_Parse(argc, argv, pl, '=');

	// Get an arguments value
	if(plib_ArgWasRun(pl[0])){
		printf("--test value: %s\n", plib_ArgGetValue(pl[0], 0, argv));
	}

	return 0;
}

--------------------------
This program uses doxygen documentation to generate documentation.
To generate the documentation please do the following

doxygen -g .plibDoxy
doxygen .plibDoxy

Now if you open the ./html/index.html in your browser you can view 
the documentation.
